comment_regular_data.body:
Personal preference:
1. rtl (errors always on the right as the most important information);
2. lose the emoji, use the diagnostics sign config and use the highlight groups from the diagnostic groups;
3. lose the OK summary; they don't provide useful information in the summary (you don't care how many checks -- out of how many? -- passed; you want to know at first glance how many failed, and where);
4. alignment isn't necessary (anything you pick is likely to be wrong for _some_ check -- treesitter parsers, I'm looking at you...)
